body:
Disclaimer: I'm brand new to verilog (but am a professional software developer).

I have been tinkering on an icebreaker FPGA dev kit for a few weeks, and I've begun reading more into setting up testbenches to properly test my designs instead of throwing them at the FPGA and seeing what happens. Thus far I've been using yosys to synthesize my verilog designs. Today I downloaded iverilog 10.3 and it began complaining about `test.v:3: error: syntax error in continuous assignment`. I reduced the verilog file to the following that still reproduces the error:
```
module test(output [WIDTH-1:0] out);
    parameter WIDTH = 16;
    assign out = WIDTH'b1;
endmodule
```
If I replace the `WIDTH'b1` with `16b1` explicitly, the syntax error vanishes. Am I doing something wrong or is this a bug?

This seems to be similar to #94 (or related?).

